Text.string: I just finished an excellent ECHOnet series. Good show, Vault Hunter!
Wainwright and I do make quite the couple. He's a little bit country, while I myself am a little bit Digby Vermouth's 9th concerto in D-minor.
Ah, yes! Conversation! Delightful.
Vault Hunter, I'm so glad you're here! Because now I can challenge you to a freestyle rap battle! En garde!
Everyone gets the blues now and again. But as a man of culture and dignity, I only get the indigos!
You certainly showed that Katagawa fellow what's what, Vault Hunter!
The Vault Key is assembled, I hear. Hear, hear!
I don't know what we'd do without you, Vault Hunter. Ah, yes. Die horribly, that's right.
I wonder how the Maliwan Corporation will soldier on without Katagawa at the helm. Yet at the same time, I don't care a whit.
Mister Strongfork wouldn't have been my first choice for an ally, but any port in a storm, I suppose. Jolly good thing it worked out.
And with that, all of our woes have come to an end. Nothing but smooth sailing from here on out, yes?
That unpleasantness reminded my of my own time in the corporate sphere. Tedious work, advertising. But without it, how would people know to want things?
What are your thoughts on that Zer0 chap? I have my own, I can tell you. But I shan't.
Strange bedfellows you've aquired, eh, Vault Hunter?
With the key to the Promethea Vault in hand, one can only speculate where fate will lead you next. As for me, I would assume it's the Vault on Promethea.
Maya's presence is already sorely missed, Vault Hunter. She can never be replaced, but she must be avenged.
My heart goes out to poor Ava. Give her my sincerest condolences, would you?

Perhaps this isn't the time, but with Maya gone, who has replaced her as a Siren? There must always be six, correct? Was Troy one already or did he become one after taking her powers? Questions abound...
Chin up, Vault Hunter. Maya wouldn't want us to be awash with grief, but rather in the blood of those who took her from us.
Death comes for us all, Vault Hunter. Small comfort in times like these, I'm sure.
Words fail me, Vault Hunter. That does not happen often, as I'm sure you're aware.
An enemy with the power to defeat Maya is not to be underestimated. Proceed with caution, Vault Hunter. We cannot afford to lose you.
These are dark times, indeed.
Now is not the time for grieving, Vault Hunter, but for action! Honor Maya's memory by saving the lives of those she cared for. That includes you.
[sigh] I... Ugh.
I shudder to think what may have befallen me had you not arrived when you did, Vault Hunter. You have my gratitude.

I'm no stranger to torture, Vault Hunter. And the warden you dispatched was nothing compared to the time I was held captive by a throng of women engaged in a bachelorette party outside of Liar's Berg. They were never violent, but the things they did to me... just gruesome.
Thank you for reuniting me with my dear Winny, Vault Hunter. My separation from him was worse than any electric nipple clamp that interrogator could have applied.
I fear my rescue cost you valuable time, Vault Hunter. If there's anything I can do to assist, please don't hesitate to ask.
I owe you my life, Vault Hunter—and a Hammerlock always pays his debts. Would you accept a post-dated check? I'm waiting on a settlement, you see.
For a moment there, I thought my head was destined to be displayed above some bandit's mantle between a pornographic magazine and... well, another pornographic magazine, most likely.

I cannot thank you enough for my freedom, Vault Hunter. No living thing deserves to be held in a cage. Stuffed and mounted in a menacing stance in the corner of an oak-paneled study, now that's another story.
My sister wasn't always like this, Vault Hunter. She used to be shorter.
Never a dull moment, eh? Ahem, yes. Sorry about that.

Imprisonment changes a man, Vault Hunter. I have become quiet, reserved, introspective. I may never again regale you with gripping tales of adventure and intrigue. Gone are the days of my long-winded yarns. I am an island unto myself, never to be reached, no matter how hard you may try. I appreciate your understanding as I struggle to navigate this new, reclusive persona that has been thrust upon me. Let us speak no more about it. Starting... now!
I can't say I'm surprised at my sister's chosen path. I expect this will make our family Mercenary Day gatherings quite awkward indeed.
Aurelia's reign of terror is coming to an end. Soon she will have to return to her previous reign of terror: demanding to speak to a manager at puppet shows.

I don't care if Winny runs a multi-trillion dollar corporation or polishes rifles for nickels outside of a bandit encampment. But if he wants to provide me with a lavish lifestyle of luxury and travel, then so help me, my baby shall do so!
For as long as Winny and I have been an item, it's surprising that this is our first time gathering an army to overthrow a wealthy tyrant.
The Jakobses are notoriously stubborn and Winny is no exception. If he aims to regain control of the family business, woe be to whomever stands in his way.
Nothing like a good old-fashioned uprising to get the blood flowing. And flow it shall, internally or otherwise!
You did it! You saved Pandora! How does it feel to be a hero, Vault Hunter?
Now that the galaxy is safe for an indeterminate period of time, perhaps Wainwright and I will take a vacation. I've heard Junpai-7 is nice this time of year.
So, the Destroyer is gone... one creature I will never hunt. What sorrow...
What-what? Terribly sorry, I thought you said something. Carry on, then.
This reminds me of the time I loitered about on Eden-3, back when I was still a young thing. Very strict loitering laws there. Ah, the recklessness of youth!
If I stand about much longer, my more artificial joints may begin to rust. Hard to sneak up on prey with a squeaking prosthetic!
Did you hear the one about the leopardmong that was spotted near the Southern Shelf? Something about all leopardmongs being spotted, I don't recall the details. Ah, humor. What fun!
I do so cherish these moments when I can be alone with my many bowel-shakingly brilliant thoughts.
Ah! My rescuer, in the flesh!
So, you've met my sister... sorry about that.
A Jakobs resistance! And here comes the spark!
So, you've seen the Jakobs' Family Jewel—that makes two of us.
You smell like mud! And betrayal! It's quite the musk!
The hero of Eden-6! Order has been restored!
You there! I have employment for you!
You're thirsting for a quest, aren't you? I'd know that look anywhere.
What's that? You want to do my bidding, do you? Well, you're in luck!
What ho! Not calling you a “ho”, mind you. I'm quite sex-positive. Just one of my many charming turns of phrase.
Well met, Vault Hunter!
So we meet again!
Hello there... you.
The sun is high and so am I! Care for a whiff of this varkid dung-sac?
Ah, daytime. Wouldn't you agree?
Look who comes gently into this dark night!
Ah, it's you! Apologies, it's dark and I've never actually cleaned this monocle.
Care to join the gig economy?
I have a quest and you have nothing better to do, by the looks of it.
Missions! Missions here!
Do what you love and you'll never work a day. But start tomorrow, I have work for you!
My kingdom for a lackey to take up this quest on my behalf!
Terribly sorry to intrude, but... how's things?
I must ask you for a status update, Vault Hunter.
Not that I expected you to be done by now, however... Why aren't you done?
Just popping in to say good luck. We're all counting on you.
This mission is of the utmost importance! And don't let the fact I've forgotten what it was disabuse you of that fact!
Tally ho!
Godspeed!
Ta ta! Oh, dear me, no. I don't believe I'll be saying that again.
Fare thee well, Vault Hunter.
Until we meet again!
Have fun surging o'er the battlements!
Ja ne!
Bon voyage!
Ciao, for the time being!
Aloha! But the “goodbye” kind, of course.
